Ubilite







































 




















UBILITE Inc. is a San Diego-based fabless semiconductor company that designs and markets Ultra Low Power (ULP) 802.11 based wireless connectivity products for the Internet of Everything (IoE). The company is a pioneer in designing Ultra Low Power (ULP), disposable and wearable Wireless Local Area Networks (WLANs), which will be used extensively in sensing, and control of consumer and enterprise applications.
Ubilite offers connectivity solutions consisting of:

Ultra Low Power 802.11 Systems on a Chip (SoC)s with 10x better power consumption than the competition, built-in IPV6 and IPV4 protocol support, wake up radio, integrated power management, sensing and control interfaces
Connectivity and application development tools and software
Embedded connectivity modules with integrated processing, energy harvesting and battery integration to be used as a development tool for Ultra Low Power and disposable IoE applications









































Technology | Ubilite







































 










Technology 











As an innovator of WLAN, UBILITE Inc., will develop the world’s lowest peak power WLAN Silicon on Chip (SoC) that will beat existing products off the shelf by at least ten fold.
Our design focuses on the following:

Ubilite’s Ultra Low Power Connectivity SoC (ULP 802.11)
This will be the first Connectivity SoC that will operate using coin cell solid state or printed batteries along with energy harvesting, leading to exceptionally long life without the need for battery replacement or recharging.

ULP 802.11’s Novel System Design

Novel Ultra Low Power RF Baseband and MAC architecture
Use of low voltage circuits
Integrated DC-DC converter supporting a multitude of power sources ranging from batteries to energy harvesting
Intelligent Power Management
Integrated interfaces for sensing, and controls
IPV6/ IPV4, and Mesh Network support
Use of latest small geometry and low power fabrication processes


Highest Battery Life
This will be the first solution that puts minimal drain on battery with well managed sleep states. The customers will be able to use the device without the need to change the batteries for exceptionally long periods and even longer through the use energy harvesting.
Low Foot Print
Our Connectivity SoC has the least memory foot print for the Firmware and Software while offering great performance and functionality.
Compatibility to existing IoE clouds
Our Connectivity SoC will have drivers that will support SEP 2.0, Zatar, Open source software from Open Interconnect Consortium and works well with Allseen Alliance stack.
Complete reference design modules and software tools for development and deployment.








 






























Careers | Ubilite







































 










Careers 











Ubilite is leading provider of Connectivity technology solutions to enable Internet of Everything (IoE). We design, develop and supply complete system-on-a-chip (SoC) solutions incorporating digital, analog and radio frequency (RF) technologies, as well as related system-level hardware and software IoE applications.
UBILITE is a company created by eminent engineers, managed by experienced industry leaders and powered by the talents of a highly diverse and motivated workforce. We support a multicultural environment and make it our business to hire, inspire and develop the very best people in the industry, worldwide.
UBILITE is looking applications from the prospective employees for following positions.  Please send an email to jobs@ubilite.com to apply.










FPGA Design Engineer



Job ID : UBIE1001
Job Area : San Diego, California
Company UBILITE
UBILITE Inc. is a San Diego-based fabless semiconductor company that designs and markets Ultra Low Power (ULP) 802.11 based wireless connectivity products for the Internet of Everything (IoE). The company is a pioneer in designing Ultra Low Power (ULP), disposable and wearable Wireless Local Area Networks (WLANs), which will be used extensively in sensing, and control of consumer and enterprise applications.
Job Overview
We are currently seeking talented FPGA engineers to support hardware development of chip test platforms. The role involves working closely with hardware engineering teams to help perform initial prototype hardware debug and distribution, and new silicon bring up. This requires the ability to debug platform and hardware, and analyze and create reports on experiments/collected data.
Qualifications

Experience in FPGA design from RTL through simulation, synthesis, and on-target verification.
Experience with Xilinx ISE for FPGA development.
Good understanding of Board Level Schematics and Layout.
Understanding and use of at least some of the flowing interfaces: JTAG, I2C, SPI, PCIe, USB, high speed ADC and DAC.
Familiar with CPU sub-system.
Familiar with SRAM, DRAM and Flash operation and interface.
Proficiency with common hardware lab test equipment (Oscilloscope, Logic Analyzer, Protocol Analyzer, spectrum analyzer, signal generator, network analyzer, JTAG debuggers etc.).
Experience programming in C/C++, Matlab, Perl/Python is a plus.
Familiar with embedded software design such as RTOS, embedded Linux, Windows device.
Hands-on experience of troubleshooting to component level for both RF analog and Digital circuits.
Self-motivated, excellent communication skills and ability to excel in a team.
Experience with WiFi product is a plus.

Education

Required: MS degree in Electrical or Computer Science.
Preferred: PhD in Electrical Engineering or Compute Science

Keywords

FPGA, RTL, PCB, Xilinx






ASIC Design Engineer



Job ID : UBIE1002
Job Area : San Diego, California
Company UBILITE
UBILITE Inc. is a San Diego-based fabless semiconductor company that designs and markets Ultra Low Power (ULP) 802.11 based wireless connectivity products for the Internet of Everything (IoE). The company is a pioneer in designing Ultra Low Power (ULP), disposable and wearable Wireless Local Area Networks (WLANs), which will be used extensively in sensing, and control of consumer and enterprise applications.
Job Overview
Our digital ASIC team is currently seeking talented candidates for digital design and implementation for our ULP WiFi chips. In this position, the designer will be responsible for design and verification of various 802.11 digital ASIC designs. In this role, you will also interact with the protocol, systems, software teams at various phase of the design flow.
Qualifications

Experience with RTL Verilog design and simulation.
Strong background in digital design is desired.
Capability to learn new skills or technologies as needed and be self-motivated.
Knowledge of 802.11 (Wireless LAN) protocol is a plus

Education

Required: MS degree in Electrical or Computer Science.
Preferred: PhD in Electrical Engineering or Compute Science

Keywords

RTL, Verilog, ASIC






ULP SoC Lead



Job ID : UBIE3005
Job Area : San Diego, California
Company UBILITE
UBILITE Inc. is a San Diego-based fabless semiconductor company that designs and markets Ultra Low Power (ULP) 802.11 based wireless connectivity products for the Internet of Everything (IoE). The company is a pioneer in designing Ultra Low Power (ULP), disposable and wearable Wireless Local Area Networks (WLANs), which will be used extensively in sensing, and control of consumer and enterprise applications.
Job Overview
Our digital ASIC team is currently seeking talented candidates for SoC design and verification for our ULP WiFi chips. Successful candidates will be responsible for Full chip design, ASIC design including architecture, integration and verification, RTL design, synthesis, and timing closure of 802.11 ULP SoC. In this role, you will also interact with the radio, protocol, systems, and software teams at various phase of the design flow.
Qualifications

A minimum of 10 years of solid experience in SoC Design, Integration, Verification, and post-Si Validation.
Developing architecture and micro-architecture from specs.
Experience with complex SoC integrations including advanced verification techniques.
Experience with Cadence Design Flow.
Understanding of various bus protocols AHB, AXI and peripherals like I2S and USB.
Understanding of CPU-Subsystem and Memory controller.
Demonstrated ability to innovate and make architectural and design trade-offs for balancing performance/power/area of designs
Experience with RTL design, synthesis, static timing analysis, formal verification, low power design, test plan development, coverage-based design verification, and/or design-for-test (DFT).
Experience in coding with Verilog and scripting languages like Perl, Python, tcl.
Strong analytical and debugging skills.
Self-motivated, excellent communication skills and ability to excel in a team environment.

Education

Required: MS degree in Electrical or Computer Science.
Preferred: PhD in Electrical Engineering or Compute Science

Keywords

SoC, ASIC, RTL, Cadence






Analog Power Management Engineer



Job ID : UBIE5003
Job Area : San Diego, California
Company UBILITE
UBILITE Inc. is a San Diego-based fabless semiconductor company that designs and markets Ultra Low Power (ULP) 802.11 based wireless connectivity products for the Internet of Everything (IoE). The company is a pioneer in designing Ultra Low Power (ULP), disposable and wearable Wireless Local Area Networks (WLANs), which will be used extensively in sensing, and control of consumer and enterprise applications.
Job Overview
Our digital ASIC team is currently seeking talented candidates for CMOS analog power management unit (PMU) for our ULP WiFi chips. Successful candidates will be responsible for PMU circuit level design of buck/boost DC-DC converters, and Low Dropout Regulators among other blocks. In this role, you will also interact with the radio, protocol, systems, and software teams at various phase of the design.
Qualifications

A minimum of 5 years of solid experience in CMOS PMU circuit level design and layout supervision.
Experience in buck and boost DC-DC converters.
Experience in Low Dropout Regulators.
Experience in voltage and current references.
Experience with Cadence Design Flow.
Strong analytical and debugging skills.
Self-motivated, excellent communication skills and ability to excel in a team environment.

Education

Required: MS degree in Electrical or Computer Science.
Preferred: PhD in Electrical Engineering or Compute Science

Keywords

PMU, DC-DC, LDO






RFIC Design Engineer



Job ID : UBIE6007
Job Area : San Diego, California
Company UBILITE
UBILITE Inc. is a San Diego-based fabless semiconductor company that designs and markets Ultra Low Power (ULP) 802.11 based wireless connectivity products for the Internet of Everything (IoE). The company is a pioneer in designing Ultra Low Power (ULP), disposable and wearable Wireless Local Area Networks (WLANs), which will be used extensively in sensing, and control of consumer and enterprise applications.
Job Overview
Our RFIC team is currently seeking talented candidates for CMOS radio and/or analog circuit designers for our ULP WiFi chips. Successful candidates will be responsible for circuit level design of various radio and/or analog blocks. In this role, you will also interact with the radio, and systems teams at various phase of the design.
Qualifications

A minimum of 2 years of solid experience in CMOS circuit level design and layout supervision.
Solid background in CMOS analog design (amplifiers, op-amps, differential circuits, …).
Experience in RF circuits is a plus.
Experience with Cadence Design Environment.
Strong analytical and debugging skills.
Strong analytical and debugging skills.
Self-motivated, excellent communication skills and ability to excel in a team environment.

Education

Required: MS degree in Electrical or Computer Science.
Preferred: PhD in Electrical Engineering or Compute Science

Keywords

CMOS, Circuits.













 

































Company | Ubilite







































 










Company 











The Internet of Everything (IoE) is connecting devices and sensors in consumer wearables, at home and in enterprise to the Internet. IoE promises significant return on investment and new application opportunities for industrial automation, asset tracking, building control, retail, automotive, home automation, consumer mobile and wearables. IoE uses the existing Internet infrastructure but builds on connecting all devices at home, office, enterprise and public networks to the cloud, enabling users to access the information and control devices remotely.
 
Ideally data communicated to and from IoE enabled things should integrate seamlessly with the current Internet Infrastructure. The prevailing ubiquitous protocol layer that can seamlessly connect things to the Internet is the IP protocol and 802.11 WLAN. However due to lack of Ultra Low Power 802.11 WLAN SoCs, other less ubiquitous low power wireless connectivity solutions have been used to connect things, thus restricting applications.
UBILITE’s Innovation
UBILITE Inc. is developing the lowest power 802.11 WLAN SoC on the market with a factor 3x better power consumption than comparable solutions while providing resilient performance. The Ultra Low Power requirements enable very long battery life, or the ability to use energy harvesting.
The SoC integrates support for IP protocol, on-board power management, and interfaces required to integrate with sensors and legacy systems. Connectivity and development software and modules are provided allowing for efficient and cost effective development, and deployment.
You can obtain more Information about the company by mailing to us at info@ubilite.com.
Copyright © 2015 Ubilite.








 






























